OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FScientists have been trying for
OL,7,Fdecades to understand what the
OL,8,Fclicking sounds might mean, ITV News'
OL,9,FSam Holder reports
OL,11,FSperm whale calls are so complex they
OL,12,Fare comparable to the human language,
OL,13,Fscientists have discovered.
OL,15,FThe claim is based on the analysis of
OL,16,Fthousands of snippets of whale clicks
OL,17,F- known as codas - by scientists
OL,18,Fstudying the animals around the island
OL,19,Fof Dominica in the Caribbean.
