OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FThey found the whales use a sort of
OL,7,F"phonetic alphabet", enabling them
OL,8,Fcreate building blocks of language
OL,9,Fsimilar to words and phrases.
OL,11,FSperm whales communicate by squeezing
OL,12,Fair through their respiratory systems
OL,13,Fto make strings of rapid clicks.
OL,15,FScientists have been trying for
OL,16,Fdecades to understand what the clicks
OL,17,Fmight mean.
