OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FBut according to Jeremy Goldbogen, an
OL,7,Fassociate professor of oceans at
OL,8,FStanford University, this new research
OL,9,Fmay have "vast implications" for how
OL,10,Fwe understand the creatures.
OL,12,FThe scientists say they have found
OL,13,Ffour basic components they think make
OL,14,Fup the whales' phonetic alphabet. This
OL,15,Falphabet can then be used by the
OL,16,Fwhales in an unlimited number of
OL,17,Fcombinations - similarly to how words
OL,18,Fare used by humans.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/6
